I was contacted and asked to come clean out a home that belonged to a recently deseased horder. 
It was a 2bed/1bath home, not too large but filled to the brim with just stuff everywhere. Thankfully this was a clean hoarder so no bugs or mice involved. I actually knew the owner of the home so we came to a verbal agreement of $275 to clean out the home and if I liked anything in good condition I could keep it. I spent 4 days in the 100Â° Texas heat removing everything, cleaning everything and even doing some light maintenance work to help him rent the place out quickly. He came out the 3rd day, to see my progress and was just praising how good it looked and me fixing the exposed electrical wires and the flooring. He went on and on thanking me, I told him id be done the following day at 3pm so he agreed to meet me there to pay me and go our merry ways. Well 3pm the next day came around and he forgot to pull money out of the bank so he wrote me a check. Still no issue, I've known him for a few years and worked with him before. I waited until the following day to go cash his check at his bank and it bounced. The teller said there wasn't enough funds to cover the check so it was declined. I called him immediately and let him know and he said he was sorry he forgot to go deposit money from another job blah blah blah, so now he would stop by my houae and pay me at 7pm that same evening. Needless to say I haven't seen this person since and I havent been paid either. Now I did get restitution by returning to the house and collecting some antiques and copper, a working John Deere mower and a few other items to make us even. But now I can't feel like I can trust people I thought I could trust. I make customers sign legal agreements now. Its just sad that no one's word is his or her bond any longer. No one can be honest and everyone is so selfish today. Oh well, I learned my lesson that day and I won't be dupped again!
